From Middle English and Old French [[coste]], from Latin [[costa]]

===Pronunciation===
*kōst, /kəʊst/, /<tt>k@Ust</tt>/

===Verb===
'''to coast''' ([[intransitive]]; [[coasts]], [[coasted]], [[coasting]])

# To [[glide]] along with no added [[energy]].
#:''When I ran out of gas, fortunately I managed to '''coast''' into a nearby gas station.''
# (''Nautical'') To sail along a coast

===Noun===
'''coast''' ([[coasts]])

#The [[shoreline]] or [[oceanfront]].

